1) AWS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) AWS stands for amazon web services.
2) It provides multiple services.
like - S3,EC2,RDM,IAM,Route53,DNS,load balancer,EBS or etc.


2) What is basic advantage of cloud?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) The basic advantage of cloud is you can take on rent it when you need , and release then back
   once you don't need.

3) IAM
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) IAM stands for identity access management.
2) IAM helps us to access securely your aws account.
3) IAM Role , IAM user, IAM Group are the features of IAM
4) IAM user means the name of people we can say - hpatil
5) IAM Group - the number of people works together like - dev, qa.
6) IAM allows us to create the user and add it into respective group , so the number
   of defined services those user can access.
7) IAM is basically restricated or whatever service your required those access get's provided to you only.

4) How to create IAM group?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to the IAM service
2) click on User group
3) Create Group
4) Enter the User group name
5) Attach permissions policies to the group
6) Create Group


5) How to create user and assing a particular group
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Goto IAM service
2) Click on the User
3) Click on the Create User
4) User name - enter the username
5) Add user to the group
6) select the group name
7) click on next
8) click on create user


6) What is the region and availablity zones?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A) Region
1) Region is nothing but a geographical area.
for - mumbai, london, paris


B) Availability zones
1) Under the regions availabilty zones are there like
   us-east-1a, us-east-1b or etc

7) What is the purpose of multiple region and data centrers
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basically the main purpose two deploy your application on multiple region is , to make your application as highly available.
for eg -- 1) Mumabai region --> two data center and 2) Paris region ---> two data center are there
this way we can spread are trafic and make are application as highly available with less latency.
Also any of region will get crashed still other region will works.

8) How to define the regional and global serivce in aws?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basically regional service , means it's available under the region , you are able to change the region of that services.

Whereas the global serivce , means it's available globally , you are not able to change the region of that service or those services not belongs to the region.







